    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>April 5 article about new push to control racial imbalance in Greenwich, Conn, public schools misstated content of advertisements placed in local newspapers by group called Concerned Citizens of Greenwich</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Thursday about a new push to confront racial imbalance in the Greenwich, Conn., public schools misstated the content of fullpage advertisements placed recently in local newspapers by a group calling itself Concerned Citizens of Greenwich. The ads raised concerns about a proposal to spend $23 million rebuilding Glenville School, and offered a broader critique of a new task force considering topics including racial balance and redistricting. The ads did not ask that neighborhood schools ''not be made to suffer in the rush to bolster other schools.''</p>
      </block>
